{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"actor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"HTTPAPIServer"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HTTPAPIServer"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a RESTful JSON API over plain HTTP, built on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Network.framework"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NWListener"},{"type":"text","text":"). It exposes endpoints for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"listing, creating, starting, stopping, and deleting VMs, as well as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"resolving VM IP addresses and performing health checks."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The server binds to localhost by default. TLS can be enabled by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"providing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NWProtocolTLS.Options"},{"type":"text","text":" at initialization; otherwise the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"server uses plain HTTP. Set the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SPOOK_API_TOKEN"},{"type":"text","text":" environment"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variable to require Bearer-token authentication on all endpoints"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"except "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/health"},{"type":"text","text":". When TLS is enabled and the server is not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"running in insecure mode, an API token is required."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Endpoints","text":"Endpoints"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Method"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inli